----------------------------------------------------------

This is the file upload application example using Spring MVC:
The source repository can be found on: 
	https://github.com/spring-guides/gs-uploading-files.git
The example guide can be found on: 
	http://spring.io/guides/gs/uploading-files/

----------------------------------------------------------

The 'original' directory contains the original completed version.
It stored uploaded file content in memory on the server.

Copyright reserved to GoPivotal(http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nd/3.0/)

----------------------------------------------------------

The 'modified' directory contains the modified version, it
	-Store the uploaded file in file system;
	-Download file from file system;

To run the application(if you are using Gradle), please:
	$./gradlew bootRun

or build the a JAR first, then run it:
	$./gradlew build
	$java -jar build/libs/gs-uploading-files-0.1.0.jar


With the server running, you need to open a browser and visit 
'http://localhost:8080/upload' to see the upload form.	
